": ["Task 2026-05-11 (NDA 2026-04-20)", "Task 2026-05-12 (Security Standards)"], "narrative": "Contracting mechanics are early but real: an NDA was executed between Temasek and Zycus on 2026-04-20 (Task 2026-05-11), and the RFI package invokes Temasek's IT Security Standards & Policies for compliance (Task 2026-05-12), signalling an InfoSec review will gate any award. No MSA/SOW, legal redline, or procurement-channel detail is yet visible because the deal sits pre-shortlist. Visibility will come once the buyer names finalists and opens security due diligence; asking procurement for the post-shortlist paper timeline would create it."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["OpportunityContactRole Wing Yu Onz Decision Maker", "Next Step 2026-05-11", "Next Step 2026-07-01 (STE reference request)"], "narrative": "No economic buyer or budget owner above procurement is identified. Contact Roles name Wing Yu Onz (Director, Procurement) as Decision Maker and PRIMARY, plus VP-level evaluators Shirley Tan, Hui Yeeng Choong and Jiahui Gan, but none is confirmed to control the commercial decision or budget. The Next Step references reaching out to STE (a Temasek-related sponsor) 'to support from back end as a high profile Temasek subsid' (Next Step 2026-05-11), which shows awareness of the need for senior backing but no mapped C-level sponsor. Identifying and reaching the person who owns the S2C budget before the shortlist decision is a ranked move."}, "decision_process": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Next Step 2026-03-20", "Task 2026-06-15 (under review)", "Task 2026-07-01 (clarifications)"], "narrative": "The buyer is running a formal, procurement-led competitive process: NDA signed 2026-04-20, RFI invitation 2026-05-11, RFI submitted 2026-06-06, submission under review from 2026-06-15, and a 60-question clarification round issued 2026-07-01 due 2026-07-15. The buyer's own roadmap (Next Step 2026-03-20) is RFI/RFP in Sep-Oct with a final decision in December.